On Thursday 04 May 2006 07:53, chandrashekhartm wrote:

> How can i put expected and actual objects in assertEqual(Object aobj, 
> Object eobj); method, 

I don't understand your problem. You just write

    assertEquals( X, Y );

where X is whatever value (object) you want, and Y is whatever value (object)
you're testing.

Examples from the codebase I'm working on:

    assertEquals( listOfStrings( "eh:/S eh:/P eh:/O" ), uris );
    assertEquals( builtinNamespaces(), ins.map.keySet() );
    assertEquals( Collections.EMPTY_SET, morse.statements );
    assertEquals( 1, r.model().listSubjects().toList().size() );

Of course you (may) need to do work to create the value you want, but that's
a different matter.
